# shadcn/ui

This project uses **shadcn/ui** for all UI elements. Do not introduce ad-hoc UI libraries or raw unstyled primitives for app chrome, forms, dialogs, navigation, tables, etc., unless there is no shadcn equivalent and the user explicitly approves an exception.

## Setup

If shadcn is not initialized (no `components.json` or CLI setup in the repo), run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding components

Prefer importing from the project’s shadcn component paths (e.g. `@/components/ui/...`) after installation. If a needed primitive is not installed, add it with the CLI, for example:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the official component name (`input`, `dialog`, `dropdown-menu`, etc.).

## Patterns

- Compose features from shadcn primitives and project wrappers; keep styling consistent with existing `tailwind` + shadcn tokens.
- When implementing new screens or controls, check whether a shadcn component already exists in the codebase before building from scratch.
